Measure 12 ounces of water and transfer.
Assemble filter cone and place dripper on a mug.
Fold and place a paper filter in the dripper to form a cone.
Grind coffee beans, then add to the filter cone.
Check water temperature.
Wet the grounds with water and wait 30 seconds.
Pour water in a circular motion, avoiding overflow.
Allow coffee to drain into the mug, then remove the dripper and discard the filter and grounds.